&lt;p&gt;Beam is seeking a highly motivated and strategic Associate Director, Investor Relations to join our growing Investor Relations and External Communications team at a pivotal moment in the company&#39;s evolution. In this role, you will support the execution of Beam&#39;s investor relations strategy and play a central part in shaping how Beam&#39;s science, pipeline, and corporate narrative are communicated to the investment community. You will partner closely with senior leadership, finance, legal, corporate communications, and program teams to translate complex clinical and scientific milestones into clear, compelling, investor-ready messaging across earnings cycles, conferences, and one-on-one engagements. This position is critical to building a best-in-class IR function as Beam transitions from a clinical-stage to commercial-stage biotechnology company delivering on the promise of base editing for patients with serious diseases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support execution of Beam’s investor relations strategy, including proactive engagement with buy-side and sell-side investors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help manage investor targeting, outreach, and meeting coordination for one-on-ones, conferences, and non-deal roadshows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track investor sentiment, ownership trends, and peer activity to inform outreach strategy and positioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a secondary point of contact for inbound investor and analyst inquiries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support continuous improvement of IR best practices and infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support preparation of key disclosures and quarterly earnings materials, including scripts, slide decks, Q&amp;amp;A documents, and press releases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help ensure accuracy, consistency, and compliance across external disclosures in coordination with legal and finance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage internal consensus models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with R&amp;amp;D, Clinical Development, Regulatory, and Commercial teams to: stay current on program updates and key milestones; translate technical data into clear, investor-relevant narratives; and support investor-facing materials related to clinical data readouts, regulatory updates, and pipeline evolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help refine and maintain Beam’s corporate narrative as the company evolves from a clinical-stage to commercial-stage biotech.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in message testing and preparation of executive spokespeople.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage updates to Beam’s investor website and coordinate with Corporate Communications on broader digital and website strategy and content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
