&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and post journal entries, including accruals, prepaid expenses, reclasses, and other recurring entries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform monthly account reconciliations and investigate and resolve reconciling items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain supporting schedules for balance sheet and income statement accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with monthly and year-end close activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support for annual financial statement audits and periodic reviews, including Sarbanes-Oxley control reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally to obtain information needed to estimate monthly accruals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with documenting accounting processes and identifying opportunities to improve efficiency and strengthen internal controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ad hoc analysis and other special projects as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Accounting and 2+ years of accounting experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous public accounting experience preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, problem-solving skills and collaborative skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work effectively with all levels in the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
